OL,6,FThe committee has urged the government
OL,7,Fto support the amendments or bring
OL,8,Fforward its own "to ensure that all
OL,9,Fthose who experience the physical and
OL,10,Femotional pain and grief of pregnancy
OL,11,Fand baby loss are able to access the
OL,12,Fsupport they need".
OL,14,FA spokesperson for the Department for
OL,15,FBusiness and Trade said: "Losing a
OL,16,Fchild at any stage is incredibly
OL,17,Fdifficult and we know many employers
OL,18,Fwill show compassion and understanding
OL,19,Fin these circumstances.
